post_text: Chanute Elementary students seem to be more excited about the thermal imaging cameras installed at school this week than the adults. Instead of using a hand held device to take the temperature of each student entering the school, these new cameras scan students entering school and register a temperature for each one, even if they arrive in a large group. If a box around around a student's head changes to red, the adult observing can pull that person out of line to double check the reading. This speeds up the process and also eliminates the close contact of taking temperatures. Three of these cameras were installed at CES, one at Royster and one at CHS. Staff continue to administer hand sanitizer.

CHS Winter Homecoming has been moved to Thursday, Jan. 30, due to a conflict with Girls Regional Wrestling. Festivities will be held during the Home basketball game vs. Iola.

Thank you for your understanding.

post_text:
November 26, 2019 Press Release
School Safety Investigation

This week, district staff and Chanute PD were made aware of a potential threat of violence toward specific students at Royster Middle School. Chanute Public Schools, the Chanute Police Department and the Neosho County Attorney were involved in determining the validity and seriousness of the threat.
This afternoon, USD 413 administration and Chanute Police Department will meet with parents of specific students who may have been the targets of the threat. Steps have been taken to create a safe learning environment in all USD 413 buildings.
Student and staff safety and health will always be our top priority each and every day. USD 413, the Chanute Police Department, and the Neosho County Attorney are committed to taking all threats seriously. Any questions regarding this matter should be directed to the USD 413 Central Office at (620) 432-2500 and/or the Chanute Police Department at (620) 431-5768.
Thank you,
Dr. Kellen J. Adams Superintendent Chanute Public Schools Chief Raymond Hale Chanute Police Department

shared_text:
Chanute High School is with Tyra Bogle.
September 26, 2019 at 4:00 PM ¬∑

Parade. Hotdogs. Cheerleaders and face painting. 413 Foundation handing out hot dogs. Families, students and community mingling, while others played on the inflatables. Thanks to all - and that means all - for making this a hometown Homecoming celebration for everyone to enjoy.
